[clarification was sought from colleagues in Bangladesh. MHJ]

[2]
Date: Thu 5 May 2011
From: Andrea Mikolon <amikolon@icddrb.org> [edited]


The Department of Livestock Services [DLS] has communicated to us
that the news report of the large cattle die-off is not correct. The
district livestock office sent a team to Char Bestin and Majher Char
(remote islands 8 hours by boat from the subdistrict office) but did
not find large cattle die-offs, however, on one island they identified
5 calf deaths in the last 2 weeks (presumptive diagnosis bovine
ephemeral fever).

Dr Salah Uddin Khan [International Centre for Diarrheal Disease
Research, Bangladesh (ICCDR,B)] continues to gather information
relating to the reports.

--
Andrea Mikolon
ICDDR,B
Dhaka, on secondment from CDC, Atlanta
USA
<amikolon@icddrb.org>

[Our heartfelt thanks to Andrea for her rapid and informative
response. And the DLS team has moved promptly. - Mod.MHJ]
